  "raw_meta_yaml": "context:\n  version: \"0.1.6\"\n\npackage:\n  name: xee-rust\n  version: ${{ version }}\n\nsource:\n  url: https://github.com/Paligo/xee/archive/refs/tags/xee-v${{ version }}.tar.gz\n  sha256: a330b26d359e83fad9b736f4ab112a907b031e9dea8523af1561d3c3a9f94be5\n\nbuild:\n  number: 1\n  script:\n    env:\n      CARGO_PROFILE_RELEASE_STRIP: symbols\n      CARGO_PROFILE_RELEASE_LTO: fat\n    content:\n      - if: unix\n        then:\n          - cargo auditable install --locked --no-track --bins --root ${{ PREFIX }} --path ./xee\n        else:\n          - cargo auditable install --locked --no-track --bins --root %LIBRARY_PREFIX% --path ./xee\n      - cargo-bundle-licenses --format yaml --output ./THIRDPARTY.yml\n\nrequirements:\n  build:\n    - ${{ stdlib('c') }}\n    - ${{ compiler('c') }}\n    - ${{ compiler('rust') }}\n    - cargo-bundle-licenses\n    - cargo-auditable\n\ntests:\n  - script:\n      - xee --help\n      - xee --version\n  - package_contents:\n      bin:\n        - xee\n      strict: true\n\nabout:\n  homepage: https://github.com/Paligo/xee\n  summary: \"Xee CLI. Swiss Army knife for XML. XPath and XSLT\"\n  description: |\n    Xee is an XML Execution Engine written in Rust. It provides\n    an almost complete XPath 3.1 implementation and a command-line\n    tool that can load XML documents, issue XPath expressions against\n    them (including in a REPL), pretty-print XML documents, and\n    transform XML documents using XSLT stylesheets.\n  license: MIT AND Unicode-3.0\n  license_file:\n    - LICENSE-MIT\n    - COPYRIGHT\n    - THIRDPARTY.yml\n  documentation: https://docs.rs/xee\n  repository: https://github.com/Paligo/xee\n\nextra:\n  recipe-maintainers:\n    - salim-b\n",
